<item>
            <title>[CXF-2437] Host not set CXFJettySslSocketConnector</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2437</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Host is not set on org.apache.cxf.transport.https_jetty.JettySslConnectorFactory so org.mortbay.jetty.bio.SocketConnector tries to use all available ip addresses. This causes problems on multi-homed systems. In our environment ip2:8443 is used by our JBoss server. We want to run a CXF-Endpoint within activemq 5.2 (camel-cxf-2.0-M3) on ip1:8443. The result is:  &quot;java.net.BindException: Address already in use&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Config sample:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	&amp;lt;cxf:cxfEndpoint id=&quot;cxfEndpoint&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
		serviceClass=&quot;xxxxx&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
		wsdlURL=&quot;abc.wsdl&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
		serviceName=&quot;abc:ABC&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
		endpointName=&quot;abc:ABC_Port&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
		address=&quot;https://server:8443/abc/service&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/cxf:cxfEndpoint&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Suse Linux, ActiveMQ 5.2, Camel 2.0-M3&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
