                            <comment id="12765856" author="dbv" created="Thu, 15 Oct 2009 01:51:08 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;Patch to add support for host attribute on jetty engine....If host is not supplied, the previous behaviour is retained (listen on all local addresses).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                &amp;lt;httpj:engine host=&quot;10.0.20.10&quot; port=&quot;19001&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                        &amp;lt;httpj:tlsServerParametersRef id=&quot;secure&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                        &amp;lt;httpj:sessionSupport&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/httpj:sessionSupport&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;/httpj:engine&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch is against 2.2.3, but it applies cleanly to 2.2.4. I&apos;ve only tested in the context of my very limited use of cxf... &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12766138" author="dkulp" created="Thu, 15 Oct 2009 17:42:46 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;Applied patch with modifications.   Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basically, I left the method on the interface that just takes the port for compatibility sake.   For the impls, just forwarded that into the new method with &quot;null&quot; for host.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
